Diary: DATE: April 12th, 2024
Stranger: I saw Pablo’s face under the flickering lights. His eyes have been replaced by camera lenses. He doesn't look around anymore; he just "scans."
Stranger: Yago was carrying a soldering iron. He wasn't fixing the servers... he was welding a neural interface directly into his own forearm. 
Stranger: Every time he sparked a connection, he laughed, but it sounded like a corrupted .wav file on loop. They are building a physical bridge for the CEO to enter our world.

