Diary: DATE: April 14th, 2024
Stranger: I made it to the fire exit, but Irene was standing there. She was the Head of Security, the only one I thought I could trust.
Stranger: "You..." she said, her voice sounding like a thousand people talking at once. "The firewall is down. Not the computer's... the one in your soul."
Stranger: I saw her hands. Her fingers had been elongated into sharp, needle-like probes. She wasn't guarding the exit; she was waiting to "upload" me.
Stranger: I managed to lock her in the stairwell, but she didn't scream. She just started reciting my search history in a dead, monotone voice.

